"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-steeplechase-tracks-most-unpredictable-misunderstood-event-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 As one of America\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s steeplechase savants, a nine-time All-American and Rio Olympics competitor, Colleen Quigley understands the calculus.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 149, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 66, \"end\": 78, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"score\": 0.9999999999863576, \"rank\": 1.3699024238080598e-11, \"text\": \"All-American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\"}, {\"begin\": 83, \"end\": 95, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.785538249787692, \"rank\": 0.2730124857320034, \"text\": \"Rio Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 108, \"end\": 123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colleen_Quigley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Colleen Quigley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colleen_Quigley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colleen_Quigley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many find her chosen track and field discipline a little \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6strange, if, that is, they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve heard of it at all.\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Happens all the time.\", \"from\": 263, \"to\": 284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The questions.\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The quizzical brows.\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 320, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The lightbulb moments.\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the range of expressions, from bemusement to wonder to the shaking of heads.\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll often get in an Uber, and the driver will ask if she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s an athlete.Yes.\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes she says no to end the conversation.\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If not, they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll ask about the sport.\", \"from\": 554, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her answers range from \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ctrack and field\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d to \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009ca field athlete\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d to the one that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s certain to provoke more questions.I compete in steeplechase.\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 743, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When they don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t know, she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll explain: it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a race, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s long and there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a lot of running.\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 845, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And while running, there are barriers to surmount, and those barriers aren\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t like normal hurdles.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are water pits to navigate.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors fall regularly\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and often spectacularly.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou have to be some sort of stupid to try and do this thing at all,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1119, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She laughs, then, when one of track\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most popular debates begins.\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1189, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the hardest event?\", \"from\": 1190, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many say the 800-meter run, because it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a nearly full sprint for two laps around a track.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some say the 1,500-meters, because it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s the same thing, but not as close to full speed throughout and yet also twice as long.\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quigley would like to add steeplechase to the debate.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1439, \"end\": 1446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9961032533001633e-24, \"text\": \"Quigley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But perhaps it shouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t be an argument at all.\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1542, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her sport requires elite endurance, for all those meters that must be run.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1618, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors must be athletic, to go over the barriers; physically tough, to withstand inevitable pain; mentally fortified, to focus while still doing everything else.\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Otherwise, they\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll land in photographs that live forever: bodies upside down, heads about to hit both water and track.\\u00c2  This race is one of track\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s most unpredictable, most strategic and least understood.\", \"from\": 1786, \"to\": 1995, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For fans ofOlympic competition, extreme sport enthusiasts or anyone who simply loves watching anything crash, steeplechase is the sport for you.\", \"from\": 1996, \"to\": 2140, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s time to Embrace the Chase, where track meets distance running meets pile-ups in car accidents meets Game of Thrones-level masochism.\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2168, \"end\": 2173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chase\", \"score\": 0.6402572724235441, \"rank\": 0.40535497451283453, \"text\": \"Chase\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chase\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chase\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First, to properly embrace, understand the basics: 3,000 meters to run, five barriers to get over and the water pit to survive.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The running unfolds on seven-and-1/2 laps on the track.\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2465, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes must gooverall barriers; failure on any one means automatic disqualification.\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On lap 1, competitors skip the water and the first barrier, which is wider than the others, owing to the propensity of participants to stay bunched together early into races.\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(Imagine leaping over one while next to other racers, all wearing track spikes.)\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2808, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After lap 1, no obstacles are skipped, which adds up to seven water leaps and 28 barriers to jump over.\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pit runs 12 feet near the end of the track\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094its width: nearly 2.3 feet; its depth: 28 inches, at the deepest point\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094where it curves before the backstretch.\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 3075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re located either inside Lane 1 or outside the last lane (often 8 or 9).\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a hurdle in front of the pit, although calling that monstrosity a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009churdle\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d fails to capture its essence.\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Think: a hurdle that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s more sturdy, that won\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t fall if anyone collides with it, and that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s wider than more \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cnormal\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d versions.\", \"from\": 3275, \"to\": 3410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That bad boy stretches 12 feet in width.\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3451, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s strategy, for sure, especially around the water pits.\", \"from\": 3453, \"to\": 3516, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Competitors most often step up, on top of the barrier, then leap as far as they can.\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Without full running momentum, though, they don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t usually clear the water pit.\", \"from\": 3602, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The general rule for an ideal sequence of steps ends with one foot in the water and the other out.\", \"from\": 3683, \"to\": 3781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those who rely more on momentum jump over the barrier and stride through the water, which means they get far more than wet.\", \"from\": 3782, \"to\": 3905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With so many other competitors, everything\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and everyone\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094gets wetter and wetter as the race unspools.\", \"from\": 3907, \"to\": 4011, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This turns steeplechase into something more likeWipeout.\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe an athlete slips on a barrier.\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe they land off-balance.\", \"from\": 4106, \"to\": 4134, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe they somersault forward.\", \"from\": 4135, \"to\": 4165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe they land\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094on one foot, body bent at a horizontal angle or, in the worst case,headfirst.\", \"from\": 4166, \"to\": 4261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe the temperatures are lower that day, making the water seeping through their shoes and socks less of an annoyance and more of a menace.\", \"from\": 4262, \"to\": 4402, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe their shoes slip and slide.\", \"from\": 4403, \"to\": 4436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They still must continue running and surmounting.\\u00c2  Let\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s run through the typical arguments against this remarkable event.\", \"from\": 4437, \"to\": 4561, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Argument 1: There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s no history.\", \"from\": 4563, \"to\": 4596, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wrong!\", \"from\": 4597, \"to\": 4603, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This event isold.It originated in the U.K., where runners bent on challenging themselves raced from one town\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s church steeple to the next, while navigating stone walls and small rivers.\", \"from\": 4604, \"to\": 4791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4642, \"end\": 4646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9997476236848633, \"rank\": 0.0002524400241912642, \"text\": \"U.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These races also borrowed from equestrian, where competitors raced horses through country sides, over hedges.\", \"from\": 4792, \"to\": 4901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4823, \"end\": 4833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1419617556874326e-14, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The modern version originated at Oxford University in the middle of the 19th century and the running distance changed several times in the early 20th century Olympic Games: 2,500 meters and 4,000 meters in Paris, 1900; 2,590 in St. Louis, 1904; 3,200 in London, 1908.\", \"from\": 4903, \"to\": 5170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4936, \"end\": 4953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"score\": 0.9997952580138321, \"rank\": 0.00011916538838675379, \"text\": \"Oxford University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oxford\"}, {\"begin\": 5109, \"end\": 5114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.067370262663954e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5157, \"end\": 5163, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999781721, \"rank\": 2.173822715080656e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By 1920, the course was standardized: 3,000 meters, five barriers\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009436 inches high for men, 30 inches for women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and the water pit.\", \"from\": 5171, \"to\": 5303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(In comparison, for track\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic hurdling events, the height of the hurdles ranges from 30 inches (women, 400 meters) to 33 (women, 100 meters) to 36 (men, 400-meters) to 42 (men, 110-meters.)\", \"from\": 5304, \"to\": 5501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Officials added women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Olympic steeplechase to the track program in 2008.\", \"from\": 5502, \"to\": 5578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Argument 2: there are no scandals, lessening suspense.\", \"from\": 5580, \"to\": 5634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wrong again!\", \"from\": 5635, \"to\": 5647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic history of steeplechase is laden with doping violations.\", \"from\": 5648, \"to\": 5716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Remember, this thing isdifficultto do.\", \"from\": 5717, \"to\": 5755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Argument 3: There aren\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t any truly elite athletes.\", \"from\": 5757, \"to\": 5809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wrong!\", \"from\": 5810, \"to\": 5816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kenyans crush the steeplechase.\", \"from\": 5817, \"to\": 5852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One male competitor from Kenya has won gold at the last eight Olympic Games, despite a late entry into the discipline.\", \"from\": 5853, \"to\": 5971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5878, \"end\": 5883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.373579402213666e-17, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country swept the event\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s podium in \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009892 and 2004.\", \"from\": 5972, \"to\": 6029, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two Michael Jordans of steeple lore\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094Kenya\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Ezekiel Kemboi and Finland\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Volmari Iso-Hollo\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094won gold, twice.\", \"from\": 6030, \"to\": 6145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6042, \"end\": 6049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\", \"score\": 0.9985059407325115, \"rank\": 0.0014962948210270014, \"text\": \"Jordans\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Grand_Prix\"}, {\"begin\": 6078, \"end\": 6092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ezekiel_Kemboi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ezekiel Kemboi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ezekiel_Kemboi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ezekiel_Kemboi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mahiedine Mekhissi-Benabbad, a retired French champion won three medals (silver in \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009908, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009912; bronze, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009916).\", \"from\": 6146, \"to\": 6258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6146, \"end\": 6173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahiedine_Mekhissi-Benabbad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mahiedine Mekhissi-Benabbad\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahiedine_Mekhissi-Benabbad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mahiedine_Mekhissi-Benabbad\"}, {\"begin\": 6185, \"end\": 6191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7373513533506925, \"rank\": 0.27690252023722706, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s competition, with its more limited history, already features four Kenyan medalists (out of 12 total medals).\", \"from\": 6259, \"to\": 6381, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There aren\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t many children who grow up dreaming of steeplechase Olympic glory, if there are any at all.\", \"from\": 6383, \"to\": 6488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Courtney Wayment finished second at the U.S. Olympic trials in June and will compete in Paris.\", \"from\": 6489, \"to\": 6583, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6489, \"end\": 6497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3946819681798663e-23, \"text\": \"Courtney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courtney_Love\"}, {\"begin\": 6577, \"end\": 6582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.067370262663954e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her father competed in steeplechase in the 1980s and made two All American teams in college, but he never pushed her into steeple.\", \"from\": 6584, \"to\": 6714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6646, \"end\": 6658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"score\": 0.9999999999608917, \"rank\": 3.951363280994076e-11, \"text\": \"All American\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/All-America\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She played soccer, took up running, became an 800-meter specialistand thenlanded in the steeplechase by choice.\", \"from\": 6715, \"to\": 6826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quigley danced and played soccer growing up, became an elite runner and came to know steeplechase when her brother began competing in it.\", \"from\": 6828, \"to\": 6965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6828, \"end\": 6835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9961032533001633e-24, \"text\": \"Quigley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even then she asked, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWhat\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s this?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d She\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099d never heard of steeplechase before.\", \"from\": 6966, \"to\": 7051, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She never considered joining him, not until a coach at Florida State saw her run and told Quigley that, if she did, the Seminoles would offer a full scholarship.\", \"from\": 7052, \"to\": 7213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7107, \"end\": 7120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_State_University\", \"score\": 0.7300270918363061, \"rank\": 0.3684895340390301, \"text\": \"Florida State\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_State_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_State_University\"}, {\"begin\": 7142, \"end\": 7149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9961032533001633e-24, \"text\": \"Quigley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\"}, {\"begin\": 7172, \"end\": 7181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_State_Seminoles_football\", \"score\": 0.9839855309808304, \"rank\": 0.01616390394283233, \"text\": \"Seminoles\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_State_Seminoles_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida_State_Seminoles_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She won a national title, steepled at the Olympics, then transitioned to triathlon.\", \"from\": 7214, \"to\": 7297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenneth Rooks went from a multi-sport athlete to \\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 the steeplechaser who fell down at the USATF outdoor championships in 2023, got up and won the damn thing.\", \"from\": 7299, \"to\": 7458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7391, \"end\": 7396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Track_&_Field\", \"score\": 0.9993189960469652, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USATF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Track_&_Field\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Track_&_Field\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He triumphed at U.S.\", \"from\": 7459, \"to\": 7479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Trials and will compete here.\", \"from\": 7480, \"to\": 7509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked whatdoesconnect all the types of athletes who end up in steeple, he says aerobic strength, dexterity and general athleticism, along with the mental fortitude to do this thing that taxes both body and mind.\\u00c2  Chari Hawkins, who will compete in Paris in the heptathlon, decidedagainstbecoming a steeplechaser.\", \"from\": 7510, \"to\": 7823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7724, \"end\": 7729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chari_River\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.54547901124085e-21, \"text\": \"Chari\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chari_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chari_River\"}, {\"begin\": 7730, \"end\": 7737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Hawkins\", \"score\": 0.9974209619881594, \"rank\": 0.002585239958965897, \"text\": \"Hawkins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Hawkins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Hawkins\"}, {\"begin\": 7759, \"end\": 7764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.067370262663954e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She loves combined events, but prefers the lighter hurdles\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the ones that fall, rather than the ones thatcausefalls.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe difference between a barrier and a hurdle is like the difference between a rubber band and a brick wall,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 7824, \"to\": 8068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cYou hit a hurdle, it topples over.\", \"from\": 8069, \"to\": 8106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have scars on my trail leg from hitting [regular] hurdles.\", \"from\": 8107, \"to\": 8167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So many bloody legs.\", \"from\": 8168, \"to\": 8188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If I were to hit a barrier, one time, my knee would be gone.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI definitely think there\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a level of crazy, for sure,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Wayment.\", \"from\": 8189, \"to\": 8330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt also takes a certain level of athleticism.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Due to the variance in backgrounds and the nature of the sport, strategy assumes paramount importance.\", \"from\": 8331, \"to\": 8486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some competitors are better runners; others, better at getting over barriers.\", \"from\": 8487, \"to\": 8564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some possess dizzying kicks down back stretches, while others favor consistency throughout.\", \"from\": 8565, \"to\": 8656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quigley points to Emma Coburn, America\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s biggest steeplechase star\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094a\\u00c2\\u00a010-time national title winner, world champion and silver medalist and three-time Olympian and bronze medalist.\", \"from\": 8658, \"to\": 8842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8658, \"end\": 8665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9961032533001633e-24, \"text\": \"Quigley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\"}, {\"begin\": 8676, \"end\": 8687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Coburn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Coburn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Coburn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Coburn\"}, {\"begin\": 8813, \"end\": 8821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8790594353660337e-13, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quigley isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t intending disrespect when she says that Coburn, an elite athlete, isn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t an Olympic-caliber one in anything but steeplechase.\", \"from\": 8843, \"to\": 8985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8843, \"end\": 8850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9961032533001633e-24, \"text\": \"Quigley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She wouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t likely qualify in running and certainly wouldn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t qualify in hurdles.\", \"from\": 8986, \"to\": 9071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s built, through a distinct combination of skills, for this specific event.\", \"from\": 9072, \"to\": 9157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In contrast, Quigley cites Krissy Gear, an American steeplechaser with \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthe most insane kick of anyone I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve ever seen in my life.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Wayment points to hurdling skills as her advantage.\", \"from\": 9158, \"to\": 9346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9171, \"end\": 9178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9961032533001633e-24, \"text\": \"Quigley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allie_Quigley\"}, {\"begin\": 9201, \"end\": 9209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999980830744063, \"rank\": 1.7775666636705884e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rooks considers himself a \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009crunning specialist.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099re all kind of weird, in our own special way,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Rooks says.\", \"from\": 9347, \"to\": 9468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The steeplechase is every Olympic ideal built into one discipline.\", \"from\": 9470, \"to\": 9536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s combined events.\", \"from\": 9537, \"to\": 9560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s human suffering.\", \"from\": 9561, \"to\": 9584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It takes more than one type of athleticism.\", \"from\": 9585, \"to\": 9628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The different factors combine to add thrill and suspense to almost every race.\", \"from\": 9629, \"to\": 9707, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt is more visible in the steeplechase with the physical barriers on the track, but the Olympic ideal is involved in every sport and event,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Rooks says.\", \"from\": 9709, \"to\": 9866, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe steeplechase just shows that in a more visible way.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s why anyone who loves sports, the human spirit or good TV should jump in and Embrace the Chase.\", \"from\": 9867, \"to\": 10033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10027, \"end\": 10032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Chase\", \"score\": 0.6402572724235441, \"rank\": 0.40535497451283453, \"text\": \"Chase\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q21562